  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. A mesh-convergence verification activity is declared and thoroughly described in prose; validation narratives reference its outputs. However, no Evidence node in this package carries a prov:wasGeneratedBy link back to that activity, leaving an activity-evidence consistency gap (W-CON-05).",
