    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factors achieving levels below required thresholds, the assessment team accepted the package on the basis that Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification demonstrated all 95th-percentile hemolysis predictions remain below the clinical threshold with margin. The mesh-convergence verification activity was cited in the decision rationale as establishing that numerical discretization error is bounded and does not materially affect the safety conclusion. Residual gaps in use error, test samples, and model form are acknowledged as limitations to be addressed in a follow-on MRL 5 assessment cycle.",
